<TITLE> Millat verdict set for Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com) - The verdict in a case filed by the Anticorruption Commission against former BNP lawmaker Rashiduzzaman Millat, his wife and son will be delivered Wednesday. The authorities have so far been unable to trace the former Member of Parliament for Jamalpur-1 constituency, or his wife and son. According to the case details, Millat concealed assets worth Tk 4.96 crore in his wealth statement submitted to the ACC. The case also alleged that he amassed wealth worth Tk 5.16 crore beyond his known sources of income, with the aid of his wife and son. In a separate case, on Nov 28 last year a court sentenced Millatin his absenceto six years' imprisonment for tax evasion. The former MP was included in an ACC list of corruption suspects published on Feb 18, 2007, shortly after the caretaker government assumed power. The list named 50 politicians, businessmen, bureaucrats and others, who were asked to submit wealth statements in their own names as well as in the names of their immediate family members within 72 hours. bdne
